<HEADLINE> Mugabe Encourages Blacks to Enter Business Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe today encouraged indigenous business people to move into
the city center's business areas which were dominated by whites.
</P>
<P>
Officially opening hardware shop wholly owned by indigenous
bussinessmen in Mutare of east Zimbabwe, Mugabe said, "the face
of the city is gradually changing to reflect the economic
development of the black indigenous business person as benefiting
a city in a truly independent country."
</P>
<P>
He said the government would continue to pursue affirming
action policies to ensure the success of the indigenization
program.
</P>
<P>
"Without mincing words, it is affirming that the indigenous
person is assisted to assume his rightful place at the helm of
the economy of Zimbabwe," Mugabe said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
