<HEADLINE> Liaoning Finds Form to Nip Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Jie Jun scored 23 points and
added 15 rebounds to lead Liaoning Hunters to a 88-82 win over
visiting Guangdong Hongyuan in the fifth round of the Chinese
Basketball League on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Hunters, last year's runners-up and fourth placer so far this
season, led Hongyuan 44-35 in the first half with well-knit
defense and effective attack inside from the 2.04-meter center Jie.
</P>
<P>
Hongyuan hit 12 three-pointers but a lack of post men proved to
be fatal to them.
</P>
<P>
"I'm not satisfied with the players' perfromance even though we
won the match," said Wu Qinglong, head coach of the Hunters. "They
failed to keep consistent and control the rebounds before the
experienced Hongyuan."
</P>
<P>
But Hongyuan's head coach Zhang Yongjun said the loss was
resonable. "We failed to regain form after the National Games in
October, so the result is normal, " Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
In the other games, Chinese Army and Shandong Baoyuan both
extended their unbeaten record to five after the Army crushed
Shenyang Army 105-74 and Baoyuan demolished Zhejiang Zhongxin
68-48.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Shougang beat the Airforce 81-62 while Shanghai
Oriental ousted Sichuan Pandas 79-64. Jiangsu Nangang, led by last
season's MVP Hu Weidong, suffered an surprise 71-77 defeat by
Jinan Army.  
</P>
</TEXT>
