<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Praises China-Vietnamese Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said
here Sunday that he is satisfied with the smooth development of
ties between China and Vietnam as well as the Communist Party of
China (CPC) and the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV).
</P>
<P>
Li, who is also member of the Standing Committee of the CPC
Central Committee, made the remarks during his talks with Le Kha
Phieu, member of the Standing Committee of the CPV Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the recent years have witnessed complete recovery
and rapid development of the relations between the two countries
and the two parties.
</P>
<P>
"Frequent contacts and exchange of views between leaders of the
two countries and parties have played an important role in
consolidating the relations," Li added.
</P>
<P>
The two countries shared many smiliar or identical views on
major international issues, he said.
</P>
<P>
Pursuing long-term good-neighborly Sino-Vietnamese ties not
only conforms to the willingness and the fundamental interests of
the two peoples, but is also beneficial to safeguarding the peace
and stability in Asia and the world, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Vietnamese people have made significant
achievements in reforms and many other aspects.
</P>
<P>
He cited CPV General Secretary Do Muoi's July visit to China as
a success, saying that during the visit, the general secretarys of
the two parties reached consensus on strengthening the friendly
cooperative ties between the two nations and parties.
</P>
<P>
It will guide the establishment of the relations of the two
countries and parties with a perspective toward the 21st century,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Phieu hailed Li's visit conducive to the strengthening of the
ties and to implementation of the consensus recently reached by
CPC General Secretary Jiang Zemin and his CPV counterpart Do
Muoi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
