<HEADLINE> China Boosts Army-People Ties in Spring Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Spring Festival, China's major
traditional holiday which falls on January 28 this year, has
always been regarded as a good opportunity to promote ties between
the armed forces, the government and the people.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Civil Affairs and the General Political
Department of the People's Liberation Army recently issued a
circular calling for activities in support of the army, granting
preferential treatment to families of servicemen, supporting the
government, and cherishing the people.
</P>
<P>
The circular calls for publicizing the army's role in
safeguarding the country's security, stability and development in
order to enhance the general public's awareness of the need to
respect the army and support its reform and development.
</P>
<P>
The circular urges all military units to ensure that soldiers
learn more about the actual national situation, exhibit total
respect for the government, cherish the people, and support the
ongoing economic reform.
</P>
<P>
The document also urges local governments and people to help
solve problems encountered by soldiers and their families, as well
as those who have devoted their lives to the revolutionary cause
led by the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
The circular notes that soldiers and local residents should
practice thrift during celebrations in the festival period.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
