<HEADLINE> Georgiev and Winarni Won Golds in Men's Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, Thailand, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria's Stefan
Georgiev claimed the gold medal of the men's 59-kg at the world
weightlifting championships Sunday, with a lower boday weight than
his nearest rival.
</P>
<P>
Georgiev and China's Le Mao Sheng both lifted a total of 295
kgs but the Bulgarian weighed in 0.4 kgs lighter than Le and so
was awarded gold.
</P>
<P>
The same body-weight rule decided the women's gold medal in the
50-kg class which went to Indonesia's Winarni, who lifted a total
of 185 kgs after snatching 80 and jerking 105.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian Izabela Dragneva, who lifted the same total of 185
kgs, had to settle for the silver medal with North Korean Ri
Yong-hwa taking bronze with 180 kgs. 
</P>
