<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Province of Guangdong Witnesses Sound Industrial Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The industrial sector in
south China's Guangdong Province, a showcase of the country's
market-oriented economic reforms, experienced healthy growth during
the first 10 months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that the province's industrial output
value for the period grew by 18.2 percent to 600.5 billion yuan in
terms of constant prices for 1990.
</P>
<P>
The output value of state-owned industrial enterprises reached
148.4 billion yuan in terms of current prices, up 9.76 percent on
the previous year's period. The collective sector recorded an
industrial output value of 146.6 billion yuan between January and
October, up 9.1 percent. The output value for other industries in
the period surged 25.1 percent to 380.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The sales-production ratio for industrial products stood at
95.58 percent, a level somewhat higher than that for the 1996
period.
</P>
<P>
The province's export value hit 220.9 billion yuan in terms
of constant prices for 1990, up 19.9 percent on the same period of
1996.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's industrial sales volume for the first three
quarters totaled 512.9 billion yuan, up 17.7 percent from the
previous year's period. Gross industrial profits soared 24 percent
to 37.1 billion yuan, with net profits surging 48.8 percent to
15.3 billion US dollars, ranking second in all provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
