<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Jolts Northeastern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring 5.7
on the Richter scale hit northeastern Japan Sunday, but there were
no immediate reports of casualties or damage.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at around 12:50 p.m., was centered 80
kilometers underground in the Pacific off Fukushima Prefecture,
northeast of Tokyo, said the Meteorological Agency.
</P>
<P>
A separate tremor measuring a magnitude of 4.3 rocked Tokyo and
its vicinity at 8:02 a.m. Its epicenter was about 60 kilometers
underground in northwestern Chiba Prefecture, east of Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
A series of minor and moderate earthquakes have jolted Tokyo
and surrounding prefectures in eastern Japan in the past few
days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
