<HEADLINE> Life Science, Chemistry Institute Set Up in Yunnan of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan University in Kunming,
capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province, recently established
the Institute of Life Science and Chemistry.
</P>
<P>
The institute's goal is to promote the use of biological and
chemical technology to promote research into life science and
chemistry subjects.
</P>
<P>
The institute was established on the basis of the university's
departments of biology, chemistry, ecology and microorganisms.
</P>
<P>
An administrative official said that Yunnan University enjoys
favorable conditions for operating the Institute of Life Science and
Chemistry, and has abundant resources related to biological and
chemical research.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that the university's staff includes a large
number of noted scholars in related fields, and that the province
is well-known as the "Home of Plants and Wild Animals".
</P>
<P>
He said the institute will focus on the research and
development of biological resources so as to meet the
province's demands for economic construction and social
development.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Province is currently formulating a plan to develop
biological products, with 18 programs expected to yield total
revenues of 100 million yuan by the end of this century.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
