<DOCNO> XIE19971207.0032 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Monthly Interbank Trading Plunges in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Official statistics show that
both the trading volume and average interest rate on interbank
funds in Shanghai dropped in November.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the Shanghai-based China Foreign
Exchange Trade System show that interbank borrowing and lending
plunged more than 50 percent to 9.57 billion yuan (1.15 billion US
dollars) in November.
</P>
<P>
The average November interest rate for interbank funds was
8.843 percent, down 0.36 percentage points on the previous month.
</P>
<P>
The most active trading was recorded for seven-day, 60-day, and
90-day transactions.
</P>
<P>
Interbank trading in bonds was generally stable in November,
despite a 38.3 percent drop in the November bond repurchasing
level to 4.94 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
