<HEADLINE> Romme Breaks 5,000 Meters World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Ducth skater Gianni Romme
broke the men's 5,000 meters speed skating world record in six
minutes 30:62 seconds at a World Cup meeting in Heerenveen,
Netherlands, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The previous record of 6:34.96 was set by Johann Olav Koss of
Norway in Lillehammer in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Romme's performance shaved the time of his compatriot Bob de
Jong who just minutes earlier had broken Koss's record with
6:33.58. 
