<HEADLINE> Chinese Scholars Discuss Protection of Historical Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XUZHOU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 250 scholars and
officials gathered in this east China city recently to discuss how
to expand the protection of historical cities in the country.
</P>
<P>
China has 99 historical cities under the State protection. The
cities represent a time span of over 5,000 years.
</P>
<P>
Rapid real estate development in recent years has seriously
threatened the ancient cities, and has led to the adoption of a number
of protection regulations.
</P>
<P>
Scholars called for protecting ancient cities as a whole,
rather than focusing protection on single sites. They also
discussed how to properly protect cities which are popular tourist
attractions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
