<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Marked Decline in China's Monthly Foreign Exchange Turnover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The foreign exchange turnover
on China's foreign exchange market dropped significantly in
November along with the rising Chinese currency.
</P>
<P>
Some 4.64 billion US dollars in foreign exchange changed hands
last month, according to the Shanghai-based China Foreign Exchange
Trade System. Said figure was down nearly 27.1 percent on the
previous month.
</P>
<P>
The total volume included 4.2 billion US dollars, 2.7 billion
Hong Kong dollars and 6.44 billion Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The average daily trading volume of 232 million US dollars in
November was 23.4 percent lower than in October.
</P>
<P>
The US dollar slide against the Chinese yuan accelerated in
November, closing the month at 8.2834, down 38 points on
October. The closing price was the lowest since May 15-16, 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong dollar closed November at 1.0715 yuan, down eight
points on the previous month, with the Japanese yen first gaining
and then losing ground against the yuan to finish November at
6.4790 yuan per 100 yen, down 4,052 points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
