<HEADLINE> Won and Lee Win Japan Challenge Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's Won Hae-Kyung won
two individual races to capture the women's overall title in the
Japan Challenge Cup short track speedskating competition in
Nobeyama on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Her compatriot, Lee Jun-Hwan won the men's 3,000-meter and
Terao Satoru prevailed in the 1,000m with Lee taking the
individual overall title.
</P>
<P>
Yang Yang of China, who shared the world title with South
Korea's Chun Lee-Kyung in March, chased hard in the women's 1,000m
final.
</P>
<P>
But Won snatched victory ahead of the two world champions to
cross the finishing line in one minute 36.167 seconds, beating
Chun by 0.092 second and Yang by 0.174.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Won also took an easy win in the 3,000m event
by clocking 5:21.064, followed by her teammate An Sang-Mi in
5:22.158 and Japanese ace Ikue Teshigawara in 5:32.087.
</P>
<P>
Won, the winner in the 1,500m on Friday, collected 15 points
from her three wins to top the standings, ahead of Yang with seven
points and Chun with six points.
</P>
<P>
Satoru Terao of Japan pushed Lee into second place to win the
men's 1,000m final in 1:35.417. But Lee won the seven-men 3,000m
final in 5:27.729, beating Japan's Naoya Tamura and Li Jiajun of
China.
</P>
<P>
The win gave Lee an additional five points to win the overall
title with 13 points, five points above Li and Terao who shared
second place.
</P>
<P>
The Japan Challenge Cup was the last leg of the five-round
ranking race series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
