<HEADLINE> China's Largest Spandex Production Base Built </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- China's largest spandex
production base has been put into production recently in the
Lianyungang Development Zone in east China's Jiangsu province.
</P>
<P>
The Zhongshan Spandex Company installed a new production line
with an annual spandex production capacity of 1,500 tons. The line
was installed at a cost 70 million yuan (8.75 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The new production line was designed by the company itself and
its installation lasted only three months.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Japanese joint venture has earned total profits of 147
million yuan (18.4 million US dollars) since the early 1990s, when
advanced technology was intrduced from Japan.  
