<HEADLINE> HK Volunteers Continue Household Visits to Promote Voter Registration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Over 30,000 young volunteers
continued their household visits for the second day today to
promote the voter registration for the election of the first
Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) next May.
</P>
<P>
The Voter Registration Week began yesterday with more than
120,000 people registered as new voters when the volunteers, "the
Voter Registration Ambassadors" (VRAs), called on them, according
to the Home Affairs Department.
</P>
<P>
The VARs aim to knock on the doors of all the two million
households in Hong Kong over the weekend. Further follow-up visits
will be conducted in the evenings of December 8 to 12 to reach
those who cannot be contacted during the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The voter registration is regarded by the Hong Kong
Registration and Electoral Office as a paramount task to ensure a
successful election of the first Legislative Council of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The deadline of the entire registration process is January 16
next year.  
</P>
