<HEADLINE> China Sets World Mark in 50-kg Class </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese strongwoman Yan Zhong
bettered the world junior record by snatching 85 kilograms in the
50-kg class at the world weightlifting championships in Chiang
Mai, Thailand, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The record was just three kilograms adrift from the world
senior mark set by compatriot Bao Yujiang in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The previous junior world record of 81 kgs was established in
May by Turkish weightlifter Esma Can.
</P>
<P>
But Yan, 19, who suffered a left elbow injury, had to forfeit
in the jerk event.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's 22-year-old Winarni took two gold medals with a
jerk of 105 kgs and a total of 185 kgs. She won the bronze in the
snatch event with 80 kgs.
</P>
<P>
In the same category, Bulgarian Izabela Dragneva took three
silver medals with an 82.5-kg lift in the snatch event, 102.5-kg
in the jerk and 185-kg overall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
