<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Opposition Parties Call Hartal in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The main opposition Bangladesh
Nationalist Party (BNP) and other six small parties have called a
country-wide dawn-to-dusk hartal today.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the hartal was to protest against what they called
the "anti-national" agreement on the Chittagong Hill Tracts (CHT)
issue which was signed in Dhaka between the government and the CHT
tribal organization on December 2.
</P>
<P>
Begum Khaleda Zia, BNP Chairperson and Leader of the Opposition
in Parliament, announced Wednesday the party's hartal program,
right after the accord was signed.
</P>
<P>
Today's hartal was culminated by the participation of some
small political parties such as Jamaat-e-Islam, the Jatiya Party
faction led by kazi Zafar Ahmed, the National Democratic Alliance
and the Jatiya Ganatantrik Party.
</P>
<P>
The BNP and other opposition parties brought out torch
processions in Dhaka and elsewhere in the country to drum up
support for today's hartal.
</P>
<P>
Besides, BNP central leaders and its front organizations met
yesterday to discuss "their preparations to make the hartal
successful."
</P>
<P>
The leaders and activists of the opposition camp had organized
a series of processions and street corner meetings against the
agreement.
</P>
<P>
The government took all precautionary measures to maintain
peace by monitoring law and order situation during hartal hours. A
heavy contingent of police and security forces were deployed at
all strategic points of the city during the hartal period.
</P>
<P>
However, ambulance, vehicles of newspapers and law enforcing
agencies, and medicine and food shops remained out of the purview
of today's hartal.
</P>
<P>
There has been no report about severe clashes between the two
sides till now.  
</P>
