<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chiluba, Mugabe to Discuss Issues Affecting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba left here today for Harare on a one-day visit, during
which he will discuss the issues affecting the sub-region with
his Zimbabwean counterpart Robert Mugabe.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents will also discuss issues concerning the
bilateral relations between the two neighbors.
</P>
<P>
When asked before departure at the Lusaka International
Airport whether the two leaders will discuss reports that former
Zambian president Kenneth Kaunda is seeking asylum in Zimbabwe,
Chiluba said that he has no official information about the
issue, the Zambia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that Kaunda, following an abortive
military coup in October to overthrow the Chiluba government, has
been seeking political asylum in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba stressed that the reports started as rumors and to
date there is no official information about them.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba is accompanied by Presidential Affairs Minister Eric
Lilwamba, Acting Foreign Affairs Minister Amussa Mwanamwambwa and
other senior government officials. 
</P>
