<HEADLINE> China Routs Uzbekistan 8-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- A below-strength Chinese team
still proved too much for Uzbekistan as the defending champion
routed the former Soviet Republic 8-0 in the group B at the 11th
Asian Women's Soccer Championship Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese girls, which were rested seven veterans hammering
DPR Korea 3-1 in their Friday's opening match by head coach Ma
Yuanan, began the killing in the 15th minute on a goal from Jin
Yan.
</P>
<P>
The young striker found a rich vein of scoringpower in the
match which saw her striking again in the 45th, 62th and 74th
minute.
</P>
<P>
The home side led 5-0 after halftime and should have changed
the scoreline more than three times in a second half where it
fluffed a dozen of gilt-edged opportunites.
</P>
<P>
Head coach Ma pat his youngsters on the back after the match
but said he had expected more goals.
</P>
<P>
"Our young players performed quite well in the match," Ma tlod
the news conference. "But they could have make more goals if they
were acting more coolly before the goal."  
</P>
</TEXT>
