<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Court Sentences Tomb Robbers to Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese court has sentenced two
men to death for stealing the heads of five ancient stone statues,
with an accomplice sentenced to eight years in prison.
</P>
<P>
Han Huamin and Sun Guobin, the principal offenders, were
sentenced to death by the court in Xianyang City, Shaanxi
Province, for stealing the heads of five stone statues buried in a
Tang Dynasty (618-907) tomb in Sanyuan County. The political
rights of the offenders have also been suspended in perpetuity.
</P>
<P>
Accessory Tu Qingmin was sentenced to eight years in prison for
leasing Han a tricycle used in the robbery.
</P>
<P>
An investigation revealed that Sun instructed Han to pillage
the tomb on the night of May 3 this year. Sun later arranged for
Han to ship the stolen objects to Guangzhou, with one relic lost
in transit. Sun sold the four remaining relics for 40,000 yuan
(4,120 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
A court representative noted that the three men confessed to
their crimes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
