<P>
CAIRO, December 6 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Assistant Secretary General
Nafis Sadik, also executive director of the U.N. Population Fund,
today praised Egypt's experiment in the family-planning and
population fields.
</P>
<P>
At a joint news conference with Egyptian Health and Population
Minister Ismail Sallam after meeting Egyptian Prime Minister Kamal
el-Ganzouri here, Sadik said the U.N. Population Fund is to
