<P>
Addressing a seminar on "Thoughts on Election Reforms"
organized by the Supreme Court Bar Association in Dhaka Saturday,
Ahmed said the parties also should not regard themselves as the
only patriots and brand others as "villains and traitors."
</P>
<P>
"The root of all the troubles lies with the political parties,"
he noted. "Political parties should change their attitude to each
other."
</P>
<P>
"Political parties must learn from the past and forget their
bitterness," the president added.
</P>
<P>
"They must look forward and concentrate on the existing
problems," he said. "They must believe in peaceful coexistence and
give up the present politics of crushing other parties, which is
impossible in this civilized world today."
</P>
<P>
Speaking of parliamentary form of democracy, the president
said: "the Opposition must work in close cooperation with the
government, but this cooperation is totally absent in our
country."
</P>
<P>
Instead of mutual understanding and harmonious relations
between the government and the opposition, there exists bitter
animosity between them, the president Ahmed. "This reflects
necessarily on all matters of state, including conduct of
elections from top to bottom."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
