<HEADLINE> Nicol Takes Third title by Winning Indian International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Peter Nicol of Scotland held
off a tough challenge from Jansher Khan of Pakistan in five games
to retain the title of the Indian international squash challenge
in Bombay for the third successive year on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Nicol rallied form one set down to overcome the current world
No.1 Khan 9-15, 15-9, 9-15, 15-12, 15-5 in 80 minutes.
</P>
<P>
It was the third title for the 23-year-old this year, following
his victories in the Egypt and Kuwait Opens.
</P>
<P>
Nicol is now a strong contender to replace Jansher as the
world's top-ranked player for the first time since September, 1993.
</P>
<P>
The new rankings will be announced by the Professional Squash
Association in January. 
</P>
