<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Arrives in Hanoi for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee, arrived here this morning to start his four-day
goodwill visit to Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Li, also Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, is making the trip at
the invitation of the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV) Central
Committee and the Fatherland Front of Vietnam Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
In a written speech given out at the airport, Li said that
China and Vietnam are good neighbors linked by mountains and
rivers, and the peoples of the two countries enjoy a time-honored
friendship.
</P>
<P>
"We are glad to see that the friendly co-operative ties between
the two countries have enjoyed complete development in recent
years, and the bilateral exchanges and cooperation have kept on
expanding in various fields," Li said.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Li will hold talks with leaders of the CPV
and Vietnamese government, and exchange views on ties between two
parties and two countries, as well as on international and
regional issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Li said he was convinced that the visit will push forward the
development of the friendly cooperative ties of the two parties
and two countries.
</P>
<P>
He continued to say that since the two countries have similar
domestic situation and pursue similar ways of development, there
is a broad future for cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that through the struggle and efforts of the two
peoples, the socialist causes of the two countries will be more
prosperous," he added. 
</P>
