<HEADLINE> Brief News From Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are news
highlights from the Southern Common Market (Mercosur):
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Uruguayan President Jose Maria Sanguinetti urged
to start as soon as possible the talks between the Mercosur and
the European Union (EU) for the creation of a free trade zone
between the two blocs.
</P>
<P>
The Uruguayan president also highlighted the EU role as the
first purchaser, first seller, and first consumer in relations
with the Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
SAO PAULO -- The Director of the World Trade Organization
(WTO), Renato Ruggiero, considered the recent three-percent
raising of the Mercosur common external tariffs (CET) as a
negative sign of regionalism.
</P>
<P>
"If Mercosur becomes a collective system of defense against
liberalization, my opinion about that zone, which is positive,
might change," Ruggiero told the Gazeta Mervcantil weekly.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- The trade deficit of Brazil rose to 1.265
billion U.S. dollars in November from 749 million dollars in
October, said Brazilian Foreign Trade Ministry.
</P>
<P>
It was the worst result for the sector since March of
this year, when the deficit reached 3.826 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
SAO PAULO -- The Mercosur members created a textile
council to address their common textile problems.
</P>
<P>
The council, according to its founders, will permit their
textile industry to discuss ways and means to promote production,
use more new technologies and improve the quality of their products.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentine oil output will rise to 46 million
tons this year, against 44 million tons of 1996, according to the
official data.
</P>
<P>
A 37-billion-cubic-meter natural gas production is expected by
the end of 1997, against the 34 billion cubic meters produced last
year.
</P>
<P>
The hydrocarbons sector is the second hard currency generator
for the country, after agriculture and livestock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
