<HEADLINE> More Japanese Aid for Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government is
going to provide a loan to Sri Lanka under the 31st Yen Loan
Package, local press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
An appraisal team will be sent to Sri Lanka soon and the amount
of the Yen loan will be decided in accordance with its
recommendations, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Under the 30th Yen Loan Package, Japan granted 277 million U.S.
dollars in loan to Sri Lanka for power, telecommunications,
social, transport and environment projects, the reports said,
quoting the head of a Japanese Foreign Ministry delegation to
Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The 12-member delegation had discussions on the issue of new
loan with Sri Lankan government officials during its stay here
last week.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the total amount of Japanese Official
Development Assistance for Sri Lanka stood at 600 billion Yen
(about 4.83 billion dollars), according to the reports.  
