<HEADLINE> Bank Sponsor System Benefits Chinese Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- A bank sponsor system in east
China's Shandong Province has helped improve efficiency at 120
industrial enterprises that have signed bank-enterprise relation
agreements since August of last year.
</P>
<P>
The 120 enterprises accounted for 31 percent of total sales of
all industrial enterprises in Shandong last year, and their
profits accounted for more than 40 percent of the province's total.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the system, banks provide enterprises with
funds and other services on a relatively fixed basis, which the
enterprises use to overcome financial difficulties and improve
economic performance.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the state-owned commercial banks had
provided the 120 enterprises with 11.7 billion yuan in funds. In
September this year, another 15 enterprises were added to the
system.
</P>
<P>
The sponsoring banks say that they will increase supervision of
the enterprises to ensure their healthy development and to reduce
financial risks for the banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
