<HEADLINE> Myanmar Appoints New National Convention Convening </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar State Peace and
Development Council (SPDC) has appointed new chairman and
vice-chairmen of the National Convention Convening Commission
(NCCC) which is to lay down principles for drawing up a new state
constitution.
</P>
<P>
According to today's official newspaper The New Light of
Myanmar, Minister for Hotels and Tourism Maj.-Gen. Saw Lwin was
named as chairman of the NCCC, and Minister for Religious Affairs
Maj-Gen. Sein Htwa and Minister for Social Welfare, Relief and
Resettlement Brig.-Gen. Pyi Sone as its vice-chairmen.
</P>
<P>
The post of chairman of the NCCC was previously held by former
Minister for Religious Affairs Lt.-Gen. Myo Nyunt who was placed
in the 14-member Advisory Group to the SPDC following its
formation and the reshuffle of the cabinet on November 15.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar National Convention, which began laying down
principles for drawing up a new state constitution in January
1993, has been adjourning since March 1996 after principles in 6
out of 15 chapters for the new state constitution had been laid
down.  
</P>
</TEXT>
