<HEADLINE> Brazilian Agricultural Products Export To Reach $15 Billion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian agricultural
products export during the 1997-98 year will reach 15 billion
U.S. dollars, a 25 percent increase over the 1996-97 period,
according to Agriculture Minister.
</P>
<P>
Areas under cultivation for the 1997-98 year went up to 23 million
hectares as against 22.3 million hectares for the 1996-97 period.
</P>
<P>
Those for soybean, cotton and rice increased by 16.3, 57, and
4.2 percent, respectively, while that for corn-growing decreased
by 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, Brazil is not self-sufficient in some agricultural
products and has to import 5.5 million tons of wheat, 400,000 tons
of cotton and 2 million tons of corn a year. 
</P>
