<HEADLINE> Russians Finish 1-2-3 in Women's Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian skaters dominated the
women's final when they made a 1-2-3 sweep at the World Junior
Figure Skating Championships in Saint John, New Brunswick, on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Julia Soldatova, second on Friday's short program, showed a
perfect performance, edging compatriot Elena Ivanova to runner-up
while Victoria Volchkova, fifth on Friday, captured the bronze
medal.
</P>
<P>
Soldatova collected four 5.7 points from the judges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
