<DOCNO> XIE19971207.0157 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Direct Election of County People's Congress in China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- As a scrutineer announced the
result of ballot counting, the 30-year-old farmer Lu Qinghua was
very excited when he got to know that he had been elected a local
deputy to his County People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The election took place on November 20 in Langxi County of east
China's Anhui Province. There are 2,370 voters in the electoral
district where Lu Qinghua lives, and 2,291 valid ballots were
recovered.
</P>
<P>
Winning 1,341 votes which exceeded half of the number of ballots
by voters participating in the election, Lu Qinghua was elected as
a local deputy.
</P>
<P>
"Thank the folks for their trust in me, and I'll live
up to their expectations," said Lu.
</P>
<P>
"Sure, I'll take the views and suggestions of my fellow farmers
to the County People's Congress and do practical things for them,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Chinese laws, local people's congresses are power
organs which take charge of examining, approving and supervising
the execution of the plans concerning local economic and social
development and other sectors.
</P>
<P>
The local congresses also elect the leading officials at the
relevant corresponding levels.
</P>
<P>
The deputies to county-level people's congress have a term
of five years. Across the country, new deputies will be
elected between the latter half of the year and the former half of
following year.
</P>
<P>
According to Yang Zaisen, now vice-chairman of the standing
committee of Langxi County People's Congress, a major feature of
the election this time was to further improve the mechanism that
more than ten voters may recommend candidates.
</P>
<P>
"Such a recommendation method is a crucial breakthrough in the
election system, for it is related to whether the deputies and
officials can really run public affairs well on behalf of the
people," Yang Zaisen said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971207.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Caldera to Inaugurate Simon Bolivar Monument in Managua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President Rafael
