<DOCNO> XIE19971207.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Direct Election of County People's Congress in China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lu Qinghua was the right candidate recommended by voters. After
graduating from middle school, he went in for house maintenance in
Wuxi City of Jiangsu Province, and returned to his hometown in
April last year to work as an accountant at his village.
</P>
<P>
Lu was not a Communist Party member, but he was able to make
clear and open accounting, winning the trust and respect from the
villagers.
</P>
<P>
In Lu's electoral district, two county-level deputies should be
elected. At the beginning, a total of ten preliminary candidates
had been recommended by voters, five of whom were recommended by
ordinary voters.
</P>
<P>
Among the three final candidates, two persons were recommended
by the joint recommendation group composed of over ten voters.
</P>
<P>
Yang Zaisen said that the standing committee of the Langxi
County People's Congress had been taking the election as an
important matter in its agenda.
</P>
<P>
After mid-September, the committee had called several meetings
to make careful preparations, working out an election schedule,
dividing electoral districts, and establishing election teams in
charge of election-related matters.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with relevant laws and regulations, Langxi County
with nearly 330,000 people were divided into 107 electoral
districts, each consisted of several voter groups with
voter-chosen heads and deputy heads.
</P>
<P>
Except those who are mentally ill or have been deprived of
political rights, all people 18 years of age up to the election
day, may be registered as voters. The roster of voters would be
put up on the wall 20 days ahead of the election.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971207.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Direct Election of County People's Congress in China (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The preliminary candidates, which have been recommended by
voters, political parties and organizations, would become formal
and final candidates through consultations.
</P>
<P>
Yang Zaisen explained that the consultation process is highly
open. Election teams would print and distribute the entire
name list of preliminary candidates to voter groups which hold
meetings to decide the final candidate in the electoral district.
</P>
<P>
Sometimes, the voter groups have heated consultations if the
candidates are rather competitive with each other, Yang said.
</P>
<P>
At last, there were 295 final candidate in the county, 1.6
times that of the county's quota of deputies. In this sense,
multi-candidate elections are held according to the law.
</P>
<P>
The names of final candidates were make public five days before
the election.
</P>
<P>
On the election day, scrutineers and ballot counters
recommended by voters organized the election. The ballots were
counted in public the same day, and election result was announced
on the spot right after the election.
</P>
<P>
That day, 185 county-level people's congress deputies were
elected as scheduled, and the participation rate of voters was as
high as 97.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The new deputies will hold their first session around
late December and early January next year.
</P>
<P>
The election in Langxi is only an epitome of the overall
situation of the country, and elections are being held in good
order in other places, said Liu Zhi, an official with the
country's National People's Congress in Beijing, who had been
inspecting the election in Langxi County. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
