<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> El Nino to Bring Drought to Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, December 6 (Xinhua) -- El Nino, an abnormal
meteorological phenomenon, will bring drought to Costa Rica next
summer, weather experts.
</P>
<P>
The mean temperature of the Pacific Ocean waters now surpassing
four degrees Celsius will worsen the situation, especially in
February, March and April, experts predicted.
</P>
<P>
The most serious drought will occur in the Chorotega region of
the Guanacaste province, while other regions of the country
including the Metropolitan area will also be affected.
</P>
<P>
However, the Aqueducts and Drainage Institute will take
preventive measures to guarantee drinking water supply for the
residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
