<HEADLINE> Czech Republic to Further Lower Customs Duties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Czech
Republic has decided to further lower average customs duties to
3.3 percent starting from January 1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The move, which involves nearly 8,000 varieties of imported
goods, is welcomed by the European Union (EU), as a "practical
measure" by the country in a bid to gain an early entry into the
organization.
</P>
<P>
It is observed that the decision was taken prior to the EU
summit on December 13 in Luxembourg.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic, which has been making active efforts to
join EU, will send President Vaclav Havel to attend the summit.
</P>
<P>
The East European country has already been chosen as a
candidate to be admitted by EU as the organization makes its
first East expansion endeavor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
