<HEADLINE> Parisi Retains WBO Super Lightweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Giovanni Parisi kept the WBO super
lightweight title for the fifth time Saturday with a unanimous
12-round decision over Jose Manuel Berdonce in Catanzaro of Italy.
</P>
<P>
The 1988 Olympic gold medalist was favored by scores of
118-111, 117-112 and 116-114 on the judges' ballots. There were no
knockdowns and the dull fight rarely saw animated exchanges
between the boxers.
</P>
<P>
Parisi, a native of nearby Vibo Valentia in southern Italy,
improved his record to 36-2-1. Berdonce is 28-2-1. 
</P>
