<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Releases American Charged with Espionage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Russian intelligence service said Richard L. Bliss, 29, was
released in Rostov-on-Don, a city 1,100 kilometers south of Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Bliss was arrested November 25 there after conducting land
surveys as a field technician employed by Qualcomm, Inc., of San
Diego, a telecommunications firm installing a cellular phone
system in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Russian agency said the decision to release Bliss is based
on "principles of humanity and the relations between our two
countries". But he is still likely to face prosecution.
</P>
<P>
Bliss is accused of surveying sensitive sites using satellite
receivers brought into Russia illegally. He has admitted
surveying, but says he is innocent of espionage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
