<DOCNO> XIE19971207.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dead Toll Reaches 24 in Irkutsk's Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian Rescuers have recovered
24 bodies of people from under the rubble in Irkutsk where An
An-124 cargo plane crashed in a residential district a few seconds
after it took off at a Irkutsk' airfield on Saturday morning,
Itar-Tass news agency reported from Irkutsk.
</P>
<P>
A duty officer of the Ministry for Emergency Situations was
quoted as reporting that there were 23 people aboard the plane,
including 17 crew members and six air company officials.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that the plane was carrying 16 crew
members and 30 passengers.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Yevgeny Zhurbenko of the Trans-Baikal regional civil
defense center of the Ministry for Emergency Situations confirmed
that the plane destroyed a 64-apartment house and damaged a
five-storey 100-apartment house, two 16-apartment wooden houses, a
three-storey school and a four-storey children's house.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers have evacuated 150 children and 10 adults. Twelve
people have been hospitalized, including seven children, five of
whom are in critical condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
